ce" name=3D"pointsadvance"></a>3.7 Other Award Redemption Options</h4>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.a. <i>Moments.</i> Members may use Po=
ints to redeem or bid on experiences and events with the Marriott Bonvoy Mo=
ments program (the =E2=80=9C<b>Moments Program</b>=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9C<b>=
Moments</b>=E2=80=9D) through the Moments online auction website: <a href=
=3D"https://moments.marriottbonvoy.com/"><u>marriottbonvoy.com/moments</u><=
/a>=E2=86=97. The terms and conditions for the Moments Program can be found=
 on its website.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.b. <i>Marriott Bonvoy Boutiques</i>. =
A Member may redeem their Points for merchandise through various brand onli=
ne retail stores. Marriott Bonvoy Points orders may only be shipped to addr=
esses within the 48 contiguous United States. Points redeemed are subject t=
o the Loyalty Program Rules along with the terms and policies of the online=
 retail stores. More information on Marriott Bonvoy Boutiques can be found =
<u><a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://www.boutiques.marriottbonvoy.com/sh=
op-with-points/" aria-label=3D"here Clickable link Opens in new tab / windo=
w">here</a></u>=E2=86=97.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.c. <i>Donate Points.</i> A Member may=
 redeem their Points toward charitable donations. Once Points are donated, =
the exchange cannot be reversed or undone. Such donation of Points is not c=
onsidered a charitable donation by the United States Internal Revenue Servi=
ce (<b>=E2=80=9CIRS=E2=80=9D</b>), and therefore is not deductible under Un=
ited States tax rules and regulations. A Member may select the charity of t=
heir choice by visiting <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://giving.marriot=
t.com/" aria-label=3D"www.giving.marriott.com Clickable link Opens in new t=
ab / window"><u>www.giving.marriott.com</u></a>=E2=86=97. Points redeemed i=
n connection with charitable donations are subject to the Program Rules alo=
ng with any applicable terms and conditions of the partner processing the d=
onations.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.d. <i>Marriott Gift Cards</i>. Member=
s may redeem their Points for Marriott Gift Cards (<b>=E2=80=9CGift Cards=
=E2=80=9D</b>), which may be used for stays, as well as at participating re=
tail, spa, golf, food and beverage outlets, and meetings expenses at the El=
igible Brands described in the Gift Cards terms and conditions available on=
 the <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://gifts.marriott.com/terms.html" ar=
ia-label=3D"Gift Cards website Clickable link Opens in new tab / window"><u=
>Gift Cards website</u></a>=E2=86=97 (the <b>=E2=80=9CGift Card Website=E2=
=80=9D</b>). Gift Cards may not be used for deposit, advance purchase or to=
 secure or confirm a reservation. Gift Cards are subject to additional term=
s and conditions available on the Gift Cards Website.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.e. <i>Merchandise and Retailer Gift C=
ards</i>. A Member may redeem his/her Points for merchandise or retailer gi=
ft cards from partners that are affiliated with the Loyalty Program includi=
ng, without limitation, the companies listed on the Loyalty Program Website=
 under =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://www.marriott.com/loyalty/redeem.mi">USE =
POINTS / AWARDS.</a>=E2=80=9D Merchandise and retailer gift cards may be is=
sued by the Company or a third-party provider and will be clearly designate=
d as such. Gift cards issued by a third-party provider are subject to addit=
ional terms and conditions imposed by the issuer/participating merchant, wh=
ich will be provided with the gift card. Acceptance of the merchandise or r=
etailer gift cards is the sole responsibility of participating merchants. P=
oints redeemed in connection with these partners are subject to the Loyalty=
 Program Rules along with any applicable terms and conditions of the partne=
r. The Loyalty Program, the Company, third-party providers and any other pa=
rticipating merchants are not responsible for replacing lost, stolen or mut=
ilated gift cards. Some merchandise or retailer gift cards require an addit=
ional charge for shipping and handling. If applicable, gift cards do not in=
clude gratuities. Gift cards will usually arrive within five to seven (5-7)=
 business days.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.f. <i>Air and Car. </i>A Member may r=
edeem his/her Points for airline tickets or car rentals from the Loyalty Pr=
ogram=E2=80=99s Air + Car partner. More information on the Air + Car progra=
m may be obtained <a target=3D"_blank" title=3D"Link to Air and Car page" h=
ref=3D"https://airandcar.marriottbonvoy.com/" aria-label=3D"here Clickable =
link Opens in new tab / window"><u>here</u></a>=E2=86=97. Points redeemed i=
n connection with this partner are subject to the Loyalty Program Rules alo=
ng with any applicable terms and conditions of the partner.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.g. <i>Cruise with Points. </i>A Membe=
r may redeem his/her Points for a cruise certificate which can be applied t=
o the purchase of a cruise booking. More information on the Cruise with Poi=
nts program may be obtained <a target=3D"_blank" title=3D"Link to Cruise wi=
th Points page" href=3D"https://cruise-with-points.marriott.com/promotion/m=
ember-benefits.do" aria-label=3D"here Clickable link Opens in new tab / win=
dow"><u>here</u></a>=E2=86=97. Points redeemed in connection with this part=
ner are subject to the Loyalty Program Rules along with any applicable term=
s and conditions of the partner. This section does not apply to The Ritz-Ca=
rlton Yacht Collection (see 1.2.a for The Ritz-Carlton Yacht Collection).</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.h. <i>Rakuten Points</i>. A Member ma=
y redeem Points for Rakuten points (=E2=80=9CRakuten Points=E2=80=9D) earne=
d through the Rakuten Points loyalty program (=E2=80=9CRakuten Points Progr=
am=E2=80=9D) at a 3 Points to 1 Rakuten Point conversion ratio through this=
 <u><a href=3D"https://www.marriott.com/loyalty/redeem/partner/convertPoint=
s.mi">website</a></u> only. Members may redeem a minimum of 3,000 Points pe=
r transaction, up to a maximum of 240,000 Points per day, for Rakuten Point=
s. Members requesting to convert Marriott Bonvoy Points to Rakuten Points m=
ust be a member of both the Marriott Bonvoy Loyalty Program and the Rakuten=
 Points Program. Members must provide their Rakuten Points Program account =
number and Marriott Bonvoy Membership Number when requesting to convert Mar=
riott Bonvoy Points to Rakuten Points. Members may only request to transfer=
 Points from their Marriott Bonvoy Account to their Rakuten Points Program =
account and may not transfer Points to the Rakuten Points Program account o=
f another individual. Please refer to the <u><a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"h=
ttps://ichiba.faq.rakuten.net/detail/000006549" aria-label=3D"Rakuten websi=
te Clickable link Opens in new tab / window">Rakuten website</a></u>=E2=86=
=97 (in Japanese) for more information on the Rakuten Points Program accoun=
t number. For details on joining the Rakuten Points Program, please refer t=
o the <u><a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://point.rakuten.co.jp/" aria-la=
bel=3D"Rakuten Points Program website Clickable link Opens in new tab / win=
dow">Rakuten Points Program website</a></u>=E2=86=97 (in Japanese) and <u><=
a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://corp.rakuten.co.jp/terms/en/index.html?=
tab=3Dpoint" aria-label=3D"terms and conditions Clickable link Opens in new=
 tab / window">terms and conditions</a></u>=E2=86=97. Marriott Bonvoy reser=
ves the right, in its sole discretion, to prevent or cancel transactions wh=
ere (i) Marriott Bonvoy has reason to believe that the identity of the Memb=
er converting the Points to Rakuten Points does not match the identity of t=
he person receiving the Rakuten Points, or (ii) Marriott Bonvoy suspects th=
ere has been fraudulent activity connected with the Points to Rakuten Point=
s conversion in relation to the Member=E2=80=99s Account. Once Points have =
been redeemed for Rakuten Points, Rakuten Points will automatically be tran=
sferred to the Member=E2=80=99s Rakuten Points Program account. In most cas=
es, Rakuten Points will be posted to a Member=E2=80=99s Rakuten Points Prog=
ram account within two (2) weeks. Once Rakuten Points are ordered to a Raku=
ten Points Program account, changes, reissuance and/or re-credit of Points =
are not allowed. The terms and conditions of the Rakuten Points Program con=
trol the redemption and distribution of Rakuten Points. The Loyalty Program=
 and Rakuten Points Program reserve the right to terminate or change the Po=
ints to Rakuten Points conversion program policies, procedures, conditions =
of participation, benefits, awards and special offers, in whole or in part,=
 at any time, with or without notice. All <u><a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"h=
ttps://corp.rakuten.co.jp/terms/en/index.html?tab=3Dpoint" aria-label=3D"te=
rms and conditions Clickable link Opens in new tab / window">terms and cond=
itions</a></u>=E2=86=97 of the Rakuten Points Program apply.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.i. <i>Transfer Points to Starbucks Re=
wards=C2=AE</i>. A Member who has linked their Account with their Starbucks=
 Rewards account may redeem their Points for Starbucks Rewards Stars (=E2=
=80=9CStars=E2=80=9D) <a href=3D"https://www.marriott.com/loyalty/redeem/pa=
rtner/convertPoints.mi"><u>here</u></a>. Points are transferred at a ratio =
of 1,000 Points to 100 Stars. Members may transfer a minimum of 1,000 Point=
s and up to 50,000 Points per day in 10 Point increments to their Starbucks=
 Rewards account. Once Points have been converted to Stars, Stars will auto=
matically be deposited into the linked Starbucks Rewards account. In most c=
ases, Stars will be posted to the Member=E2=80=99s linked Starbucks Rewards=
 account within 2 business days. Once a request to transfer Points to Stars=
 has been submitted by a Member, it cannot be cancelled, changed, or refund=
ed, and all <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://www.starbucks.com/rewards/=
terms/" aria-label=3D"Starbucks Rewards Terms of Use Clickable link Opens i=
n new tab / window"><u>Starbucks Rewards Terms of Use</u></a>=E2=86=97 appl=
y, including Star expiry. Stars cannot be transferred back to Points. Marri=
ott Bonvoy reserves the right, in its sole discretion, to prevent or cancel=
 transactions where (i) Marriott Bonvoy has reason to believe that the iden=
tity of the Member converting the Points to Stars does not match the identi=
ty of the person receiving the Stars, or (ii) Marriott Bonvoy suspects ther=
e has been fraudulent activity connected with the Points to Stars conversio=
n in relation to the Member=E2=80=99s Account. For more information or to l=
ink your accounts, go to <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://www.starbucks=
.com/rewards/partnerships/marriottbonvoy" aria-label=3D"starbucks.com/marri=
ottbonvoy Clickable link Opens in new tab / window"><u>starbucks.com/marrio=
ttbonvoy</u></a>=E2=86=97.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;">3.7.j. <i>Marriott Bonvoy + MGM Rewards=
=E2=84=A2 - Dual Program Points Transfer</i>. A member of both Marriott Bon=
voy and MGM Rewards (=E2=80=9C<b>Joint Member</b>=E2=80=9D) may transfer th=
eir Points to MGM Rewards points (=E2=80=9C<b>MGM Points</b>=E2=80=9D), or =
MGM Points to Points, in accordance with the <a href=3D"https://www.marriot=
t.com/loyalty/terms/supplemental-terms/mgm-collection.mi"><u>MGM Collection=
 with Marriott Bonvoy Terms</u></a> at a ratio of eight (8) points received=
 for every ten (10) points transferred (i.e., ten (10) MGM Points transferr=
ed from the MGM Rewards Program to the Marriott Bonvoy Loyalty Program are =
converted to eight (8) Points and ten (10) Points transferred from the Marr=
iott Bonvoy Loyalty Program to the MGM Rewards Program are converted to eig=
ht (8) MGM Points). Transfers from Points to MGM Points must be initiated o=
n the <a></a><a href=3D"https://www.marriott.com/sign-in.mi?returnTo=3D%2Fl=
oyalty%2Fredeem%2Fpartner%2FconvertPoints.mi"><u>Marriott Bonvoy transfer s=
ite</u></a>. Transfers from MGM Points to Points must be initiated on the M=
GM Rewards transfer site. Joint Members must transfer a minimum of 1,000 Po=
ints to MGM Points (or 1,000 MGM Points to Points) per Dual Program Points =
Transfer transaction. Joint Members cannot transfer more than 30,000 Points=
 to MGM Points, or transfer more than 30,000 MGM Points to Points in a cale=
ndar year.</p>
