<p style=3D"margin-left: 80.0px;">i. <i>Ambassador Service</i>. An Ambassad=
or Elite Member is eligible to participate in Ambassador Service during an =
Eligible Status Year and continue through the subsequent calendar year. Amb=
assador Service is a benefit that permits an eligible Member to receive cer=
tain additional benefits as further described <a href=3D"https://www.marrio=
tt.com/loyalty/member-benefits/ambassador.mi"><u>here</u></a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 80.0px;">ii. <i>Your24</i>=E2=84=A2. Ambassador El=
ite Members are eligible to participate in Your24 during the Eligible Statu=
s Year and to continue through the subsequent calendar year. Your24 is a be=
nefit that permits an eligible Member to request a specific check-in time f=
or any upcoming stay at any Participating Property. If the requested check-=
in time is confirmed, the check-out time will be set for the same time on t=
he day of departure.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">A. Your24 benefits may be requested when=
 an Ambassador Elite Member requests a specific check-in time and check-out=
 time for a stay through Ambassador Service. Your24 benefits may also be re=
quested by an Ambassador Elite Member at any time prior to 3 p.m. (local ti=
me of the Participating Property) two (2) days prior to arrival for such st=
ay by contacting Ambassador Service. If a request for Your24 benefits is ap=
proved, Ambassador Service will connect with the Member to confirm the chec=
k-in and check-out times.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">B. Your24 benefits are subject to availa=
bility and may only be requested in connection with a stay.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">C. Your24 benefits are limited to one (1=
) room per eligible Member per Stay regardless of how many rooms have been =
reserved.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">D. If the check-in time approved for an =
Ambassador Elite Member is between 9 a.m. and 4 p.m. (local time of the Par=
ticipating Property) they may request the Platinum Elite and above benefit =
of late checkout.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">E. If the specific room type reserved by=
 an eligible Member is not available upon check-in, the Participating Prope=
rty will honour the confirmed Your24 request by temporarily providing anoth=
er room and then moving the applicable guest(s) to the reserved room type o=
nce available.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">F. Marriott Vacation Club, Marriott Gran=
d Residence Club, Sheraton Vacation Club, Westin Vacation Club, Design Hote=
ls, StudioRes, and MGM Collection with Marriott Bonvoy properties, and at T=
he Ritz-Carlton Residences, Waikiki Beach, Atlantis, Paradise Island, Baham=
as, and The Phoenician Residences, a Luxury Collection Residence Club, Scot=
tsdale do not provide Your24 benefits.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 80.0px;">iii. <i>Additional benefits at Ritz-Carlt=
on Reserve</i>. In addition to the above benefits, Ambassador Elite Members=
 will receive one $150 U.S. dollars resort credit (=E2=80=9C<b>Resort Credi=
t</b>=E2=80=9D) per Stay for each guest room under the Member=E2=80=99s nam=
e and Membership Account. Resort Credit is valid for use toward expenses ch=
arged to the room folio except for the room rate and room taxes. Ambassador=
 Elite Members staying under a promotional room rate or rate plan that alre=
ady includes resort credit will not receive the additional $150 U.S. dollar=
s Resort Credit. Resort Credit is not refundable, exchangeable, replaceable=
 or transferable for cash, gift card or other type of credit.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 80.0px;">iv. <i>Additional benefit offering at Tri=
bute Portfolio properties that are part of the partnership with Delonix Gro=
up.</i> Ambassador Elite Members will receive an additional on-property ben=
efit for each Delonix Stay for which they designate the Loyalty Program as =
primary. The benefit will be offered upon check-in, and may vary by Partici=
pating Property. This benefit is limited to the eligible Ambassador Elite M=
ember plus one (1) guest staying in the same room. It is limited to one (1)=
 guest room per Delonix Stay, regardless of how many rooms have been reserv=
ed, and the room must be under the Ambassador Elite Member=E2=80=99s name a=
nd they must stay in the guest room and pay for the charges.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 80.0px;">v. <i>Ambassador Experiential Benefit at =
Outdoor Collection by Marriott Bonvoy.</i> Ambassador Elite members will re=
ceive an additional and distinct exclusive offering (including food and bev=
erage offerings, discounts, amenities, and more) upon check-in. The benefit=
 may vary by Participating Property and is subject to change.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 80.0px;">vi. <i>Ambassador Plus One Benefit</i>. E=
ligible Ambassador Elite Members have the ability to grant Ambassador Elite=
 status to another Member (the =E2=80=9C<b>Plus One Benefit</b>=E2=80=9D), =
subject to the following terms:</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(A) To be eligible for the Plus One Bene=
fit, a Member must (i) have status of Ambassador Elite or above, (ii) have =
achieved one hundred (100) Elite Night Credits, and (iii) spend $40,000 of =
Annual Qualifying Spend (thus becoming an =E2=80=9C<b>Achieving Member</b>=
=E2=80=9D). An Achieving Member may gift Ambassador Elite status to a compa=
nion, spouse, or significant other (=E2=80=9C<b>Recipient Member</b>=E2=80=
=9D).</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(B) The Recipient Member and the Achievi=
ng Member must reside at the same address and have the same address listed =
on their Marriott Bonvoy Account. The Recipient Member must (i) be the gift=
ing Achieving Member=E2=80=99s companion, spouse, or significant other, and=
 (ii) not yet have achieved Ambassador Elite Membership Status within the c=
urrent Eligible Status Year, as defined in Section 4.2.e. Please be aware t=
hat any suspected fraud will be thoroughly investigated, and if confirmed, =
both Accounts=E2=80=99 will be revoked.=E2=80=AFIf the Recipient Member=E2=
=80=99s account is closed due to fraud or abuse, the Achieving Member=E2=80=
=99s account may be subject to review, forfeiture of the Plus One Benefit, =
and potential closure at the sole discretion of the Loyalty Program.&nbsp;<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(C) The Elite Status of the Recipient Me=
mber will be upgraded within forty-eight (48) hours after the Achieving Mem=
ber=E2=80=99s Ambassador receives adequate supporting documentation confirm=
ing the selected Recipient Member=E2=80=99s eligibility for the status upgr=
ade. The Recipient Member will hold Ambassador Elite status for a minimum o=
f a full calendar year. For example, if a Member is given the Ambassador El=
ite status benefit before the February 1, 2027, deadline for Elite status r=
enewal, the Member will enjoy Ambassador Elite status for the remainder of =
2026 (depending on the date of Plus One Benefit selection), which will cont=
inue through 2027 and expire by February 2028.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(D) To maintain the Plus One Benefit, th=
e Achieving Member must meet the requirements set forth in Section 4.3.e.vi=
.A of the Marriott Bonvoy Program Rules, in the subsequent Eligible Status =
Year (2027 in the example above) to retain the Achieving Member=E2=80=99s o=
wn status and the Recipient Member=E2=80=99s Ambassador Elite status during=
 the following calendar year (2028 in the example above). If the Achieving =
Member does not achieve the Ambassador Elite status needed to keep the Plus=
 One Benefit, both the Achieving Member and the Recipient Member will be do=
wngraded to Titanium Elite status in March of the calendar year following s=
uch subsequent Eligible Status Year (2028 in the example above). The Recipi=
ent Member can only keep Ambassador Elite status when the Achieving Member =
re-earns the Plus One Benefit and continues to authorize Recipient Member=
=E2=80=99s Account for the Plus One Benefit or when the Recipient Member ac=
hieves Ambassador Elite status on their own.&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(E) Under no circumstances will the Loya=
lty Program provide Achieving Members or Receiving Members any Membership d=
etails or personal Member information in order to facilitate the Plus One B=
enefit.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(F) If the desired recipient of the Plus=
 One Benefit is not currently a Member, then desired recipient must registe=
r at <a href=3D"https://www.marriott.com/loyalty/createAccount/createAccoun=
tPage1.mi?EnrollmentSourceCode=3DAPO1">marriottbonvoy.com/join</a> before t=
he Plus One Benefit can be provided. Additionally, the Recipient Member can=
not be a Marriott associate.&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(G) For any changes to your Plus One Ben=
efit recipient, reach out to <a href=3D"mailto:ambassador.service@marriott.=
com">Ambassador Service</a> or your personal Ambassador for a one-time chan=
ge.&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 120.0px;">(H) The Recipient Member will be assigne=
d to the personal Ambassador of the Achieving Member. If the personal Ambas=
sador of the Achieving Member changes, the Receiving Member=E2=80=99s perso=
nal Ambassador will update accordingly. Only the Achieving Recipient can re=
quest a change to their personal Ambassador.</p>
